        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Insisting that the world provide you with",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "better opportunities",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is a way to hide. A way to hide from your feelings of disappointment and inadequacy, from your fear of uncertainty, and from your aversion to imperfection.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s also largely a crutch, because every time you pass up a ‘faulty’ opportunity for a potentially better one that hasn’t shown up yet, you can avoid the internal conflict of",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "choosing wrong",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://blog.brendanbockes.com/but-what-if-i-choose-wrong/"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It takes guts to choose from what’s available. To stop waiting for a better, more explicit option. But it’s also the only way to ever move forward, because perfect will never come.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Waiting to find a faultless opportunity is a delusion, and a self-sustaining one. It’s up to us to lean in and make the imperfect",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "better",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "—to make the best out of what comes up.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
